abstract_ssm: The Blackout Arts Collective, started in New York City in 1997, is a group of artists, community organizers, students, teachers, professionals, entrepreneurs, and formerly incarcerated individuals working to empower communities of color through the arts, activism and education. This collection consists of their administrative records.
